liebertGlobalProductsPowerModule.name: liebertGlobalProductsPowerModule

Replaced INTEGER with Integer32 (SMIv2). Minor spelling fixes and formatting.

lgpPwrBattery.name: lgpPwrBattery
lgpPwrBattery.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert Power Battery object identifiers.
lgpPwrBattery.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Power Battery Group.

lgpPwrMeasurements.name: lgpPwrMeasurements
lgpPwrMeasurements.description: This sub-tree registers Liebert Power Measurement object identifiers. The sub-tree contains tables and well known power measurement points.
lgpPwrMeasurements.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Power Measurement Group.

lgpPwrStatus.name: lgpPwrStatus
lgpPwrStatus.description: This sub-tree registers Liebert Power Status object identifiers. This is the location of power related status information that does not fit into a more specific category such as the lgpPwrConversion sub-tree.
lgpPwrStatus.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Power Status Group

lgpPwrSettings.name: lgpPwrSettings
lgpPwrSettings.description: This sub-tree registers Liebert Power Static Switch object identifiers.
lgpPwrSettings.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Power Settings Group.

lgpPwrConversion.name: lgpPwrConversion
lgpPwrConversion.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert Power Conversion object identifiers.
lgpPwrConversion.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Power Conversion Group.

lgpPwrControl.name: lgpPwrControl
lgpPwrControl.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert Power Control object identifiers.
lgpPwrControl.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Power Control Group.

lgpPwrTopology.name: lgpPwrTopology
lgpPwrTopology.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert Power Topology object identifiers.
lgpPwrTopology.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Power Topology Group.

lgpPwrStatistic.name: lgpPwrStatistic
lgpPwrStatistic.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert Power Statistic object identifiers.
lgpPwrStatistic.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Power Statistic Group.

lgpPwrConfig.name: lgpPwrConfig
lgpPwrConfig.description: This sub-tree is used to register Liebert Power Configuration Object identifiers.
lgpPwrConfig.reference: The registrations for the objects in this sub-tree are defined below in the sub-section titled Liebert Power Configuration Group.

lgpPwrNumberInstalledBatteryModules.name: lgpPwrNumberInstalledBatteryModules
lgpPwrNumberInstalledBatteryModules.description: The number of battery modules installed in the device.

lgpPwrNumberFailedBatteryModules.name: lgpPwrNumberFailedBatteryModules
lgpPwrNumberFailedBatteryModules.description: The number of battery modules in the device that have failed.

lgpPwrNumberRedundantBatteryModules.name: lgpPwrNumberRedundantBatteryModules
lgpPwrNumberRedundantBatteryModules.description: The number of redundant battery modules in the device.

lgpPwrNumberActiveBatteryModules.name: lgpPwrNumberActiveBatteryModules
lgpPwrNumberActiveBatteryModules.description: The number of active battery modules in the device.

lgpPwrConfigLowBatteryWarningTime.name: lgpPwrConfigLowBatteryWarningTime
lgpPwrConfigLowBatteryWarningTime.description: The value of the device's estimated minutes of remaining battery at which a lgpEventLowBatteryWarning notification will be sent.

lgpPwrNumberBatteryModuleWarnings.name: lgpPwrNumberBatteryModuleWarnings
lgpPwrNumberBatteryModuleWarnings.description: The number of battery modules in the device that have a warning.

lgpPwrBatteryTestResult.name: lgpPwrBatteryTestResult
lgpPwrBatteryTestResult.description: The outcome of the previous battery test.

lgpPwrNominalBatteryCapacity.name: lgpPwrNominalBatteryCapacity
lgpPwrNominalBatteryCapacity.description: The nominal battery capacity of the system (in minutes) at full load.

lgpPwrBatteryFloatVoltage.name: lgpPwrBatteryFloatVoltage
lgpPwrBatteryFloatVoltage.description: The battery float voltage of the system.

lgpPwrBatteryEndOfDischargeVoltage.name: lgpPwrBatteryEndOfDischargeVoltage
lgpPwrBatteryEndOfDischargeVoltage.description: The battery voltage threshold at which the batteries are considered completely discharged.

lgpPwrAutomaticBatteryTestCountdown.name: lgpPwrAutomaticBatteryTestCountdown
lgpPwrAutomaticBatteryTestCountdown.description: The time remaining before the next battery test.

lgpPwrBatteryChargeStatus.name: lgpPwrBatteryChargeStatus
lgpPwrBatteryChargeStatus.description: The present state of the system's battery charge. A value of 'charging' indicates the batteries are currently charging. A value of 'discharging' indicates the batteries are currently discharging. A value of 'fullycharged' indicates the batteries are charged to their full capacity. A value of 'notfullycharged' indicates the battery charge is neither fully charged, charging or discharging.

lgpPwrBatteryLifeEnhancer.name: lgpPwrBatteryLifeEnhancer
lgpPwrBatteryLifeEnhancer.description: The state of the battery life enhancer. When 'on', it will preserve battery life.

lgpPwrBatteryCharger.name: lgpPwrBatteryCharger
lgpPwrBatteryCharger.description: The state of the battery charger.

lgpPwrBatteryChargeMode.name: lgpPwrBatteryChargeMode
lgpPwrBatteryChargeMode.description: The mode of the battery charger: 'float' charging or 'equalize' charging.

lgpPwrBatteryTimeRemaining.name: lgpPwrBatteryTimeRemaining
lgpPwrBatteryTimeRemaining.description: An estimate of the time to battery charge depletion under the present load conditions if the utility power is off and remains off, or if it were to be lost and remain off. NOTE: A UPS is expected to provide a battery time remaining value when not operating on battery. However, if the system is not capable of providing this information, then this point will return 65535 to indicate that the value is unavailable.

lgpPwrBatteryCapacity.name: lgpPwrBatteryCapacity
lgpPwrBatteryCapacity.description: The present percentage of battery capacity.

lgpPwrBatteryCabinet.name: lgpPwrBatteryCabinet
lgpPwrBatteryCabinet.description: This sub-tree contains items related to battery cabinets.

lgpPwrBatteryCabinetCount.name: lgpPwrBatteryCabinetCount
lgpPwrBatteryCabinetCount.description: The number of battery cabinets installed with this device. Note some devices may not permit writing a value to this object.

lgpPwrBatteryCabinetType.name: lgpPwrBatteryCabinetType
lgpPwrBatteryCabinetType.description: The type of battery cabinet(s) installed on this device. Enumeration definitions: notSpecified - The type has not been specified in the device's configuration. internal - Battery cabinets are internal to the device. external - Device has external battery cabinets installed. lrt - Long Run Time cabinets. Note some devices may not permit writing a value to this object.

lgpPwrBatteryCabinetRatedCapacity.name: lgpPwrBatteryCabinetRatedCapacity
lgpPwrBatteryCabinetRatedCapacity.description: Battery cabinet rated capacity (tenths of Amp-hours). This assumes that each cabinet is of the same type and capacity. This is not a sum of the rating for all attached cabinets. Note some devices may not permit writing a value to this object.

lgpPwrBatteryLeadAcidCellCount.name: lgpPwrBatteryLeadAcidCellCount
lgpPwrBatteryLeadAcidCellCount.description: Battery cell count - lead-acid. The number of cells that comprise the lead acid battery string.

lgpPwrBatteryNiCadCellCount.name: lgpPwrBatteryNiCadCellCount
lgpPwrBatteryNiCadCellCount.description: Battery cell count - nickel-cadmium. The number of cells that comprise the nickel-cadmium battery string.

lgpPwrBatteryAmpHoursConsumed.name: lgpPwrBatteryAmpHoursConsumed
lgpPwrBatteryAmpHoursConsumed.description: The cumulative battery Amp-hours withdrawn over the life of the battery. This value persists across reboots. Typically, this value is reset back to zero when the batteries are replaced.

lgpPwrBatteryAmpHoursDischargeConsumed.name: lgpPwrBatteryAmpHoursDischargeConsumed
lgpPwrBatteryAmpHoursDischargeConsumed.description: The battery Amp-hours withdrawn during the current/latest discharge. This value does not persist across reboots.

lgpPwrBatteryLastDischargeTime.name: lgpPwrBatteryLastDischargeTime
lgpPwrBatteryLastDischargeTime.description: The date and time of the last battery discharge. Typically this is the time when the discharge starts. This value persists across reboots. The date and time are determined in seconds since the epoch on January 1, 1970.

lgpPwrBatteryLastCommissionTime.name: lgpPwrBatteryLastCommissionTime
lgpPwrBatteryLastCommissionTime.description: The date and time when the battery system was put into service. This information persists across system reboot events. It is the responsibility of Service to reset this date/time when the batteries are replaced. The date and time are determined in seconds since the epoch on January 1, 1970.

lgpPwrBatteryPresentDischargeTime.name: lgpPwrBatteryPresentDischargeTime
lgpPwrBatteryPresentDischargeTime.description: The total time spent on battery during the current or last discharge. NOTE: While not discharging, some systems may display zero instead of the last discharge.

lgpPwrBatteryCapacityStatus.name: lgpPwrBatteryCapacityStatus
lgpPwrBatteryCapacityStatus.description: The indication of the capacity remaining in the UPS system's batteries. NOTE: In a single-module system, this point is intended to have the same behavior as the RFC1628 point upsBatteryStatus.

lgpPwrBatteryCircuitBreakerState.name: lgpPwrBatteryCircuitBreakerState
lgpPwrBatteryCircuitBreakerState.description: The state of the Battery Circuit Breaker.

lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints.name: lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints
lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints.description: This sub-tree registers well known Liebert Power Measurement Points. The object identifier names usually imply locations where the measurement is taken -- such as 'input', 'output' and 'bypass'.
lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints.reference: These well known measurement identifiers are referenced in the 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' column in the 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable'.

lgpPwrSource1Input.name: lgpPwrSource1Input
lgpPwrSource1Input.description: This sub-tree is used to register a source 1 input as a well known measurement point. It is intended that no sub-trees be created below this node. Power input to the managed device from power source 1. Many power systems contain more than one input source and many of them have more than one measurement point per input source. This identifier represents one input source for the system but does not necessarily represent the 'first' one. The input sources' numbering with respect to 'lgpPwrSource1Input' etc. may depend on the physical wiring of the system when it was installed.

lgpPwrSource2Input.name: lgpPwrSource2Input
lgpPwrSource2Input.description: This sub-tree is used to register a source 2 input as a well known measurement point. It is intended that no sub-trees be created below this node. Power input to the managed device from power source 2. Many power systems contain more than one input source and many of them have more than one measurement point per input source. This identifier represents one input source for the system but does not necessarily represent the 'first' one. The input sources' numbering with respect to 'lgpPwrSource2Input' etc. may depend on the physical wiring of the system when it was installed.

lgpPwrSourcePdu1Input.name: lgpPwrSourcePdu1Input
lgpPwrSourcePdu1Input.description: This sub-tree is used to register a source PDU 1 input as a well known measurement point. It is intended that no sub-trees be created below this node. Power input to the managed device from power distribution unit 1. Many power systems contain more than one input source and many of them have more than one measurement point per input source. This identifier represents one input source for the system but does not necessarily represent the 'first' one. The input sources' numbering with respect to 'lgpPwrSourcePdu1Input' etc. may depend on the physical wiring of the system when it was installed.

lgpPwrSourcePdu2Input.name: lgpPwrSourcePdu2Input
lgpPwrSourcePdu2Input.description: This sub-tree is used to register a source PDU 2 input as a well known measurement point. It is intended that no sub-trees be created below this node. Power input to the managed device from power distribution unit 1. Many power systems contain more than one input source and many of them have more than one measurement point per input source. This identifier represents one input source for the system but does not necessarily represent the 'first' one. The input sources' numbering with respect to 'lgpPwrSourcePdu2Input' etc. may depend on the physical wiring of the system when it was installed.

lgpPwrOutputToLoad.name: lgpPwrOutputToLoad
lgpPwrOutputToLoad.description: This sub-tree is used to register the output to the critical load as a well known measurement point. It is intended that no sub-trees be created below this node.

lgpPwrMeasBattery.name: lgpPwrMeasBattery
lgpPwrMeasBattery.description: This sub-tree is used to register a battery as a well known measurement point. It is intended that no sub-trees be created below this node.

lgpPwrMeasBypass.name: lgpPwrMeasBypass
lgpPwrMeasBypass.description: This sub-tree is used to register a bypass as a well known measurement point. It is intended that no sub-trees be created below this node.

lgpPwrMeasDcBus.name: lgpPwrMeasDcBus
lgpPwrMeasDcBus.description: This sub-tree is used to register a DC bus as a well known measurement point. It is intended that no sub-trees be created below this node.

lgpPwrMeasSystemOutput.name: lgpPwrMeasSystemOutput
lgpPwrMeasSystemOutput.description: This sub-tree is used to register the output of a multi-module system as a well known measurement point. It is intended that no sub-trees be created below this node. This identifier represents the power related data of the system.

lgpPwrMeasBatteryCabinet.name: lgpPwrMeasBatteryCabinet
lgpPwrMeasBatteryCabinet.description: This sub-tree is used to register the voltage between the most negative and the most postive terminals of a battery cabinet. To determine the cabinet being described in a multi-cabinet system, this point implements an additional two indexes. The first index describes the module the cabinet is located in. The second index describes the cabinet number. In an SMS(Single-Module System) the first index is always 1. Example: lgpPwrMeasBatteryCabinet.2.4 'lgpPwrMeasBatteryCabinet' = Point is a battery cabinet. '.2' = Cabinet is in the second module. '.4' = Cabinet number 4

lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable
lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.reference: The measurement points represented by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' can be found in the sub-tree lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints. Additional measurement detail on a 'per line' basis is available in the lgpPwrLineMeasurementTable
lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.description: This table contains a list of AC power measurement point entries. The table contains zero, one, or many rows, depending upon the number of power related measurement points available. The NMS cannot create or delete rows from the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the managed device. Each row in the table represents a series of measurements on a given point or location within the system. Measurement points/locations are identified by the object identifier 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the 'LgpPwrMeasurementPointEntry' object. The actual measurement being taken at that identified point is identified by the other corresponding columns in the LgpPwrMeasurementPointEntry for the particular row of the table.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointEntry.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointEntry
lgpPwrMeasurementPointEntry.description: This entry defines the measurements to be populated in the various columns of the 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable'.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointIndex.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointIndex
lgpPwrMeasurementPointIndex.description: This is the index that indicates the row of the 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable' for a power measurement point.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointId.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointId
lgpPwrMeasurementPointId.reference: The object identifiers in this column can be found in the sub-tree 'lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints'.
lgpPwrMeasurementPointId.description: An OID representing a well known measurement point. These object identifiers indicate a point or location of power measurement in a power system. The OID's name usually implies a location of the measurement point such as 'input', 'output', 'bypass' etc.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointNumLines.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointNumLines
lgpPwrMeasurementPointNumLines.description: The number of lines on the indicated power measurement point. (i.e. the number of phases on the power source being measured.)

lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomVolts.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomVolts
lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomVolts.description: The magnitude of the nominal voltage on the power source being measured.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomFrequency.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomFrequency
lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomFrequency.description: The nominal or configured/expected frequency for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointFrequency.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointFrequency
lgpPwrMeasurementPointFrequency.description: The present (actual) frequency for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointApparentPower.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointApparentPower
lgpPwrMeasurementPointApparentPower.description: The present apparent AC power for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointTruePower.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointTruePower
lgpPwrMeasurementPointTruePower.description: The present AC power for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointPowerFactor.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointPowerFactor
lgpPwrMeasurementPointPowerFactor.description: The present Power Factor for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointWattHours.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointWattHours
lgpPwrMeasurementPointWattHours.description: The present number of Watt Hours for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointVAPercent.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointVAPercent
lgpPwrMeasurementPointVAPercent.description: The percentage of the rated apparent AC power of the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointNeutralCurrent.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointNeutralCurrent
lgpPwrMeasurementPointNeutralCurrent.description: The present neutral current of the power point indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointGroundCurrent.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointGroundCurrent
lgpPwrMeasurementPointGroundCurrent.description: The present ground current of the power point indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomCurrent.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomCurrent
lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomCurrent.description: The nominal or configured/expected current of the power point indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomPowerFactor.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomPowerFactor
lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomPowerFactor.description: The nominal or configured/expected power factor of the power point indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomVA.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomVA
lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomVA.description: The nominal or configured/expected apparent AC power for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomW.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomW
lgpPwrMeasurementPointNomW.description: The nominal or configured/expected true AC power for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrMeasurementPointPowerFactorTag.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPointPowerFactorTag
lgpPwrMeasurementPointPowerFactorTag.description: The present description of the Power Factor for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable. If Leading, the load is said to be capacitive and the phase of the current leads the voltage. If Lagging, the load is said to be inductive and the phase of the current lags the voltage.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementTable.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementTable
lgpPwrLineMeasurementTable.description: A list of power measurements for each phase/line for a given power measurement point/location in the 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable'. The lgpPwrMeasurementPointIndex in this table corresponds to the index in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable. This table contains zero, one, or many rows, depending upon the number of power line source objects available. The NMS cannot create or delete rows from the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the managed device.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementEntry.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementEntry
lgpPwrLineMeasurementEntry.reference: The lgpPwrMeasurementPointIndex can be found in the lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable. This index identifies the measurement point for which the line detail measurement in the table applies.
lgpPwrLineMeasurementEntry.description: This entry defines the contents of the columns for the table 'lgpPwrLineMeasurementTable'.

lgpPwrMeasurementPtIndex.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPtIndex
lgpPwrMeasurementPtIndex.description: This is the index indicating the row of the table 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable' for a power measurement point.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementIndex.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementIndex
lgpPwrLineMeasurementIndex.description: This is the index indicating the row of the table 'lgpPwrLineMeasurementTable' for a power measurement point.

lgpPwrMeasurementPoint.name: lgpPwrMeasurementPoint
lgpPwrMeasurementPoint.reference: The object identifiers in this column can be found in the sub-tree 'lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints' and correspond to the entry in the table lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable.
lgpPwrMeasurementPoint.description: An OID representing a well known measurement point. These object identifiers indicate a point or location of power measurement in a power system. The OID name usually implies a location of the measurement point such as 'input', 'output', 'bypass', etc.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementVoltsLL.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementVoltsLL
lgpPwrLineMeasurementVoltsLL.description: The present Line-to-Line voltage measurement for the indicated source. The line being measured is given by the lgpPwrLineMeasurementIndex [1 = AB, 2 = BC, 3 = CA].

lgpPwrLineMeasurementVoltsLN.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementVoltsLN
lgpPwrLineMeasurementVoltsLN.description: The present Line-to-neutral voltage measurement for the indicated source. The line being measured is given by the lgpPwrLineMeasurementIndex where [1 = A, 2 = B, 3 = C].

lgpPwrLineMeasurementCurrent.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementCurrent
lgpPwrLineMeasurementCurrent.description: The present current measurement for the indicated source. The line being measured is given by the 'lgpPwrLineMeasurementIndex' where [1 = A, 2 = B, 3 = C].

lgpPwrLineMeasurementCapacity.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementCapacity
lgpPwrLineMeasurementCapacity.description: The percentage of the power capacity presently being used on this line.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementVA.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementVA
lgpPwrLineMeasurementVA.description: The present apparent AC line power.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementTruePower.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementTruePower
lgpPwrLineMeasurementTruePower.description: The present AC line power measured in watts.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementVoltageTHD.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementVoltageTHD
lgpPwrLineMeasurementVoltageTHD.description: The present total harmonic distortion on the AC line voltage.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementCurrentTHD.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementCurrentTHD
lgpPwrLineMeasurementCurrentTHD.description: The present total harmonic distortion on the AC line current.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementCrestFactorCurrent.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementCrestFactorCurrent
lgpPwrLineMeasurementCrestFactorCurrent.description: The present crest factor of the line current.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementPowerFactor.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementPowerFactor
lgpPwrLineMeasurementPowerFactor.description: The present Power Factor for the line.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementPowerFactorTag.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementPowerFactorTag
lgpPwrLineMeasurementPowerFactorTag.description: The present description of the Power Factor for the line. If Leading, the load is said to be capacitive and the phase of the current leads the voltage. If Lagging, the load is said to be inductive and the phase of the current lags the voltage.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementMaxVolts.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementMaxVolts
lgpPwrLineMeasurementMaxVolts.description: The maximum voltage measurement recorded for the indicated source since the command 'lgpPwrStatisticsReset' was executed.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementMinVolts.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementMinVolts
lgpPwrLineMeasurementMinVolts.description: The minimum voltage measurement recorded for the indicated source since the command 'lgpPwrStatisticsReset' was executed.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementVAR.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementVAR
lgpPwrLineMeasurementVAR.description: The present reactive AC line power of the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrMeasurementPoint'.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementPercentLoad.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementPercentLoad
lgpPwrLineMeasurementPercentLoad.description: The present percent load of the AC line power.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementVolts.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementVolts
lgpPwrLineMeasurementVolts.description: The present voltage measurement for the indicated source.

lgpPwrLineMeasurementVACapacity.name: lgpPwrLineMeasurementVACapacity
lgpPwrLineMeasurementVACapacity.description: The percentage of the apparent power capacity presently being used on this line.

lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTable.name: lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTable
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTable.reference: The measurement points represented by 'lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId' can be found in the sub-tree lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints. Additional measurement detail on a 'per line' basis is available in the lgpPwrLineMeasurementTable
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTable.description: This table contains a list of DC power measurement point entries. The table contains zero, one, or many rows, depending upon the number of power related measurement points available. The NMS cannot create or delete rows from the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the managed device. Each row in the table represents a series of measurements on a given point or location within the system. Measurement points/locations are identified by the object identifier 'lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId' in the 'LgpPwrDcMeasurementPointEntry' object. The actual measurement being taken at that identified point is identified by the other corresponding columns in the LgpPwrDcMeasurementPointEntry for the particular row of the table.

lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointEntry.name: lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointEntry
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointEntry.description: This entry defines the measurements to be populated in the various columns of the 'lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTable'.

lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointIndex.name: lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointIndex
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointIndex.description: This is the index that indicates the row of the 'lgpPwrMeasurementPointTable' for a power measurement point.

lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId.name: lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId.reference: The object identifiers in this column can be found in the sub-tree 'lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints'.
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId.description: An OID representing a well known measurement point. These object identifiers indicate a point or location of power measurement in a power system. The OID's name usually implies a location of the measurement point such as 'input', 'output', 'bypass' etc.

lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointSubID.name: lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointSubID
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointSubID.description: The identifier used to differentiate between identical thresholds for a given point index and point ID in the DC measurements table.

lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointVolts.name: lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointVolts
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointVolts.description: The present DC voltage for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointCurrent.name: lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointCurrent
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointCurrent.description: The present DC current for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointNomVolts.name: lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointNomVolts
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointNomVolts.description: The nominal(configured/expected) DC voltage for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTruePower.name: lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTruePower
lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTruePower.description: The present DC power for the power source indicated by 'lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointId' in the corresponding row in the lgpPwrDcMeasurementPointTable.

lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementTypes.name: lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementTypes
lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementTypes.description: This sub-tree registers well known Liebert Power Measurement Types. The object identifier names usually encompass units of measure, lines of reference, and device location. The OID's name usually implies a measurement type such as 'voltsAC', 'current', 'voltsDc', 'VoltsLL', etc.

lgpPwrVoltsAc.name: lgpPwrVoltsAc
lgpPwrVoltsAc.description: This identifier represents an AC voltage.

lgpPwrVoltsDc.name: lgpPwrVoltsDc
lgpPwrVoltsDc.description: This identifier represents a DC voltage.

lgpPwrAmpsNeutral.name: lgpPwrAmpsNeutral
lgpPwrAmpsNeutral.description: This identifier represents a current measurement in Amps on the neutral line.

lgpPwrWellKnownControlPoints.name: lgpPwrWellKnownControlPoints
lgpPwrWellKnownControlPoints.description: This sub-tree registers well known Liebert Power Control Points. The object identifier names usually imply locations where control of a device is available -- such 'output' or 'load circuits'.
lgpPwrWellKnownControlPoints.reference: These well known control identifiers are referenced in the 'lgpPwrLoadCircuitId' column in the 'lgpPwrLoadCircuitTable'.

lgpPwrLoadCircuit.name: lgpPwrLoadCircuit
lgpPwrLoadCircuit.description: The managed device's controllable load circuit. Many power systems contain more than one load circuit. This identifier represents one load circuit for the system but does not necessarily represent the 'first' one. The load circuits' numbering with respect to 'lgpPwrLoadCircuit1' etc. may depend on the physical wiring of the system when it was installed.

lgpPwrLoadCircuitTable.name: lgpPwrLoadCircuitTable
lgpPwrLoadCircuitTable.description: A list of load circuits that can be controlled(opened or closed). The NMS cannot create or delete rows from the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the managed device.

lgpPwrLoadCircuitEntry.name: lgpPwrLoadCircuitEntry
lgpPwrLoadCircuitEntry.description: This entry defines the contents of the columns for the table 'lgpPwrLoadCircuitTable'.

lgpPwrLoadCircuitIndex.name: lgpPwrLoadCircuitIndex
lgpPwrLoadCircuitIndex.description: This is the index indicating the row of the table 'lgpPwrLoadCircuitTable'.

lgpPwrLoadCircuitId.name: lgpPwrLoadCircuitId
lgpPwrLoadCircuitId.reference: The object identifiers in this column can be found in the sub-tree 'lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints'.
lgpPwrLoadCircuitId.description: An OID representing a well known load circuit identifier. These load circuit identifiers indicate the name or type of load circuit reference in the table.

lgpPwrLoadCircuitSubID.name: lgpPwrLoadCircuitSubID
lgpPwrLoadCircuitSubID.description: This is a sub identifier for the 'lgpPwrLoadCircuitId'. It indicates the hardware identifier of the load control circuit.

lgpPwrLoadCircuitState.name: lgpPwrLoadCircuitState
lgpPwrLoadCircuitState.description: This identifier indicates the state of the load circuit. When read, only a closed or open response will be returned. When written to, the state of the circuit will transition to desired state.

lgpPwrLoadCircuitStateAndControl.name: lgpPwrLoadCircuitStateAndControl
lgpPwrLoadCircuitStateAndControl.description: This identifier indicates the state of the load circuit. When read, only a closed or open response will be returned. When written to, the state of the circuit will transition to desired state.

lgpPwrAlarmSilence.name: lgpPwrAlarmSilence
lgpPwrAlarmSilence.description: Audible Alarm Silence Command. This command turns off the device's audible alarm. It will not affect the status of the alarm(s) that caused the audible alarm. This command should be sent with a parameter of 1. This variable doesn't return a value when read.

lgpPwrBatteryTest.name: lgpPwrBatteryTest
lgpPwrBatteryTest.description: Battery Test Command. This command will initiate a battery test if one is not already in progress, or abort the current test if it is in progress.

lgpPwrUpsAbortCommand.name: lgpPwrUpsAbortCommand
lgpPwrUpsAbortCommand.description: UPS Abort command. This command will abort the pending command on the device. There is no guarantee a client using the abort command will cancel a command sent moments before from the same client. Another client could initiate a command and change what command is actually pending on the device. This command should be sent with a parameter of 1. This variable doesn't return a value when read.

lgpPwrTransferToBypass.name: lgpPwrTransferToBypass
lgpPwrTransferToBypass.description: Transfer to Bypass Command. This command will initiate a transfer of the load to the bypass of the system. This command should be sent with a parameter of 1. This variable doesn't return a value when read.

lgpPwrTransferToInverter.name: lgpPwrTransferToInverter
lgpPwrTransferToInverter.description: Transfer to Inverter Command. This command will initiate a transfer of the load to the inverter of the system. This command should be sent with a parameter of 1. This variable doesn't return a value when read.

lgpPwrOutputOnDelay.name: lgpPwrOutputOnDelay
lgpPwrOutputOnDelay.description: Output On Delay Command. This command will turn on the output of the device after a user specified delay. The number of seconds to delay is subject to the precision of the device and should be kept to 10 second intervals.

lgpPwrOutputOffDelayWithRestart.name: lgpPwrOutputOffDelayWithRestart
lgpPwrOutputOffDelayWithRestart.description: Output Off Delay with Restart Command. This command will turn off the output of the device after a user specified delay. The number of seconds to delay is subject to the precision of the device and should be kept to 10 second intervals. The device will then turn the output on again after a specified amount of time.

lgpPwrOutputOffDelayWithoutRestart.name: lgpPwrOutputOffDelayWithoutRestart
lgpPwrOutputOffDelayWithoutRestart.description: Output Off Delay without Restart Command. This command will turn off the output of the device after a specified delay. The number of seconds to delay is subject to the precision of the device and should be kept to 10 second intervals. The device will NOT automatically turn the output on following this command.

lgpPwrTransferCount.name: lgpPwrTransferCount
lgpPwrTransferCount.description: Number of times that the output load has been transferred between the available input sources.

lgpPwrAutoTransferTimer.name: lgpPwrAutoTransferTimer
lgpPwrAutoTransferTimer.description: The required wait time between output load auto transfer attempts between available input sources.

lgpPwrAutoReTransferEnabled.name: lgpPwrAutoReTransferEnabled
lgpPwrAutoReTransferEnabled.description: The ability to retransfer the output load automatically to the well known measurement source from the 'lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurements' sub-tree that is the preferred input source of the system

lgpPwrSyncPhaseAngle.name: lgpPwrSyncPhaseAngle
lgpPwrSyncPhaseAngle.description: The phase angle difference of source 1 in relation to source 2.

lgpPwrParallelSystemOutputToLoadSource.name: lgpPwrParallelSystemOutputToLoadSource
lgpPwrParallelSystemOutputToLoadSource.description: The source supporting the parallel system's load.

lgpPwrDcToDcConverter.name: lgpPwrDcToDcConverter
lgpPwrDcToDcConverter.description: The state of the DC to DC converter.

lgpPwrOutputToLoadOnInverter.name: lgpPwrOutputToLoadOnInverter
lgpPwrOutputToLoadOnInverter.description: The present source of output power is the Inverter.

lgpPwrBatteryChargeCompensating.name: lgpPwrBatteryChargeCompensating
lgpPwrBatteryChargeCompensating.description: The system is adjusting the battery charging algorithm to accommodate for the battery temperature.

lgpPwrInverterReady.name: lgpPwrInverterReady
lgpPwrInverterReady.description: The ability of the inverter to support the output load of the system.

lgpPwrOutputToLoadOnBypass.name: lgpPwrOutputToLoadOnBypass
lgpPwrOutputToLoadOnBypass.description: The present source of output power is the Bypass.

lgpPwrBoost.name: lgpPwrBoost
lgpPwrBoost.description: The present state of the boost circuitry

lgpPwrBuck.name: lgpPwrBuck
lgpPwrBuck.description: The present state of the buck circuitry

lgpPwrShutdownOverTemperature.name: lgpPwrShutdownOverTemperature
lgpPwrShutdownOverTemperature.description: The system has previously shutdown due to an over temperature condition.

lgpPwrShutdownOverload.name: lgpPwrShutdownOverload
lgpPwrShutdownOverload.description: The system has previously shutdown due to an over load condition.

lgpPwrShutdownDcBusOverload.name: lgpPwrShutdownDcBusOverload
lgpPwrShutdownDcBusOverload.description: The system has previously shutdown due to a DC bus over load condition.

lgpPwrShutdownOutputShort.name: lgpPwrShutdownOutputShort
lgpPwrShutdownOutputShort.description: The system has previously shutdown due to an output short condition.

lgpPwrShutdownLineSwap.name: lgpPwrShutdownLineSwap
lgpPwrShutdownLineSwap.description: The system has previously shutdown due to a condition where the line and neutral were reversed.

lgpPwrShutdownLowBattery.name: lgpPwrShutdownLowBattery
lgpPwrShutdownLowBattery.description: The system has previously shutdown due to a low battery condition.

lgpPwrShutdownRemote.name: lgpPwrShutdownRemote
lgpPwrShutdownRemote.description: The system has previously shutdown due to a remote shutdown command.

lgpPwrShutdownInputUnderVoltage.name: lgpPwrShutdownInputUnderVoltage
lgpPwrShutdownInputUnderVoltage.description: The system has previously shutdown due to an under voltage condition during startup.

lgpPwrShutdownPowerFactorCorrectionFailu.name: lgpPwrShutdownPowerFactorCorrectionFailure
lgpPwrShutdownPowerFactorCorrectionFailu.description: The system has previously shutdown due to a power factor correction startup failure.

lgpPwrShutdownHardware.name: lgpPwrShutdownHardware
lgpPwrShutdownHardware.description: The system has previously shutdown due external shutdown signal.

lgpPwrRedundantSubModule.name: lgpPwrRedundantSubModule
lgpPwrRedundantSubModule.description: The system has a redundant battery module installed.

lgpPwrBypassReady.name: lgpPwrBypassReady
lgpPwrBypassReady.description: The ability of the bypass to support the output load of the system. If Yes, the bypass is available to transfer to.

lgpPwrGeneratorStatus.name: lgpPwrGeneratorStatus
lgpPwrGeneratorStatus.description: The state of the system generator.

lgpPwrRotaryBreakerStatus.name: lgpPwrRotaryBreakerStatus
lgpPwrRotaryBreakerStatus.description: The state of the system rotary breaker.

lgpPwrPowerFactorCorrection.name: lgpPwrPowerFactorCorrection
lgpPwrPowerFactorCorrection.description: The state of the power factor correction circuitry of the system.

lgpPwrBypassSyncDiff.name: lgpPwrBypassSyncDiff
lgpPwrBypassSyncDiff.description: The phase angle difference between the inverter output and bypass source. A positive value means the inverter leads the bypass source. A negative value means the inverter lags the bypass source.

lgpPwrBypassOverloadShutdownTime.name: lgpPwrBypassOverloadShutdownTime
lgpPwrBypassOverloadShutdownTime.description: The calculated time remaining before bypass static switch shutdown due to the present overload condition. If the bypass is not in an overload condition, this object returns -1.

lgpPwrInverterOverloadShutdownTime.name: lgpPwrInverterOverloadShutdownTime
lgpPwrInverterOverloadShutdownTime.description: The calculated time remaining before inverter shutdown. The calculated time of inverter operation remaining for the present overload event. Note: If the inverter is not experiencing an overload event this point will return 65535 indicating this value is unavailable.

lgpPwrStateOutputSource.name: lgpPwrStateOutputSource
lgpPwrStateOutputSource.description: The UPS's output power source (inverter, bypass, or none). NOTE: It is possible that the load still has power from the Maintenance Bypass.

lgpPwrStateInputSource.name: lgpPwrStateInputSource
lgpPwrStateInputSource.description: The system input power source (none, utility, generator).

lgpPwrStateInputQualification.name: lgpPwrStateInputQualification
lgpPwrStateInputQualification.description: The current state of the system input. The unit may or may not operate normally under 'marginalLow' and 'marginalHigh' states.

lgpPwrStateBypassStaticSwitchState.name: lgpPwrStateBypassStaticSwitchState
lgpPwrStateBypassStaticSwitchState.description: The current state of the bypass static switch.

lgpPwrStateBypassQualification.name: lgpPwrStateBypassQualification
lgpPwrStateBypassQualification.description: The current operational state of the bypass static switch. The unit may or may not operate normally under 'marginalLow' and 'marginalHigh' states.

lgpPwrStateDCBusQualification.name: lgpPwrStateDCBusQualification
lgpPwrStateDCBusQualification.description: The current operational state of the DC bus. The unit may or may not operate normally under 'marginalLow' and 'marginalHigh' states.

lgpPwrStateOutQualification.name: lgpPwrStateOutQualification
lgpPwrStateOutQualification.description: The current operational state of the output. The unit may or may not operate normally under 'marginalLow' and 'marginalHigh' states.

lgpPwrStateInverterQualification.name: lgpPwrStateInverterQualification
lgpPwrStateInverterQualification.description: The current operational state of the inverter. The unit may or may not operate normally under 'marginalLow' and 'marginalHigh' states.

lgpPwrStateInverterState.name: lgpPwrStateInverterState
lgpPwrStateInverterState.description: The current state of the inverter.

lgpPwrStateRectifierState.name: lgpPwrStateRectifierState
lgpPwrStateRectifierState.description: The current state of the rectifier.

lgpPwrStateModuleGroup.name: lgpPwrStateModuleGroup
lgpPwrStateModuleGroup.description: This group contains UPS module information.

lgpPwrStateUpsModuleCount.name: lgpPwrStateUpsModuleCount
lgpPwrStateUpsModuleCount.description: Number of UPS modules in the system. In a single module system, this value is one.

lgpPwrStateUpsModuleRedundantCount.name: lgpPwrStateUpsModuleRedundantCount
lgpPwrStateUpsModuleRedundantCount.description: Number of redundant UPS modules in the system. In a single module system, the value is zero. This value is dependent upon the present load and the number of modules (i.e. the value may change during normal operation based upon a load change). This value represents the number of extra modules above the minimum needed to support the load.

lgpPwrStateBackfeedBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateBackfeedBrkrState
lgpPwrStateBackfeedBrkrState.description: The state of the Static Bypass Switch Line Disconnect Breaker.

lgpPwrStateLoadDisconnectState.name: lgpPwrStateLoadDisconnectState
lgpPwrStateLoadDisconnectState.description: The state of the Static Bypass Switch Load Disconnect Breaker.

lgpPwrStateInputBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateInputBrkrState
lgpPwrStateInputBrkrState.description: The state of the Input Disconnect Breaker.

lgpPwrStateTrapFilterBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateTrapFilterBrkrState
lgpPwrStateTrapFilterBrkrState.description: The state of the Trap Filter Disconnect Breaker.

lgpPwrStateInvOutputBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateInvOutputBrkrState
lgpPwrStateInvOutputBrkrState.description: The state of the Inverter Output Disconnect Breaker.

lgpPwrStateIntBypassBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateIntBypassBrkrState
lgpPwrStateIntBypassBrkrState.description: The state of the Internal Bypass Breaker.

lgpPwrStateBypassIsolBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateBypassIsolBrkrState
lgpPwrStateBypassIsolBrkrState.description: The state of the Bypass Isolation Breaker.

lgpPwrStateRectifierIsolBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateRectifierIsolBrkrState
lgpPwrStateRectifierIsolBrkrState.description: The state of the Rectifier Isolation Breaker.

lgpPwrStateMaintBypassBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateMaintBypassBrkrState
lgpPwrStateMaintBypassBrkrState.description: The state of the Maintenance Bypass Breaker.

lgpPwrStateMaintIsolBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateMaintIsolBrkrState
lgpPwrStateMaintIsolBrkrState.description: The state of the Maintenance Isolation Breaker.

lgpPwrStateOutStaticSwState.name: lgpPwrStateOutStaticSwState
lgpPwrStateOutStaticSwState.description: The state of the Output Series Static Switch.

lgpPwrStateModuleOutBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateModuleOutBrkrState
lgpPwrStateModuleOutBrkrState.description: The state of the Module Output Breaker.

lgpPwrBypassReXfrRemainTime.name: lgpPwrBypassReXfrRemainTime
lgpPwrBypassReXfrRemainTime.description: The time remaining before an inverter overload or inverter fault can be cleared and auto retransfer from the bypass to the inverter can take place. Note: If an inverter overload or fault is not taking place, this point will return 65535.

lgpPwrStateUpsOutputSource.name: lgpPwrStateUpsOutputSource
lgpPwrStateUpsOutputSource.description: The present source of output power. The enumeration none(2) indicates that there is no source of output power (and therefore no output power), for example, the system has opened the output breaker. NOTE: In a single-module system, this point is intended to have the same behavior as the RFC1628 point upsOutputSource.

lgpPwrStateLoadBusSynchronization.name: lgpPwrStateLoadBusSynchronization
lgpPwrStateLoadBusSynchronization.description: The state of the Load Bus Synchronizer (LBS).

lgpPwrStateCircuitBrkrStateGroup.name: lgpPwrStateCircuitBrkrStateGroup
lgpPwrStateCircuitBrkrStateGroup.description: This group contains Static Switch circuit breaker state information.

lgpPwrStateSource1InputBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateSource1InputBrkrState
lgpPwrStateSource1InputBrkrState.description: The states of Source 1 Input Breaker.

lgpPwrStateSource2InputBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateSource2InputBrkrState
lgpPwrStateSource2InputBrkrState.description: The states of Source 2 Input Breaker.

lgpPwrStateSource1BypassBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateSource1BypassBrkrState
lgpPwrStateSource1BypassBrkrState.description: The states of Source 1 Bypass Breaker.

lgpPwrStateSource2BypassBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateSource2BypassBrkrState
lgpPwrStateSource2BypassBrkrState.description: The states of Source 2 Bypass Breaker.

lgpPwrStateAuxOutputBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateAuxOutputBrkrState
lgpPwrStateAuxOutputBrkrState.description: The states of Auxiliary Output Breaker.

lgpPwrStateSource1PduInputBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateSource1PduInputBrkrState
lgpPwrStateSource1PduInputBrkrState.description: The states of Source 1 PDU Input Breaker.

lgpPwrStateSource2PduInputBrkrState.name: lgpPwrStateSource2PduInputBrkrState
lgpPwrStateSource2PduInputBrkrState.description: The states of Source 2 PDU Input Breaker.

lgpPwrEconomicOperation.name: lgpPwrEconomicOperation
lgpPwrEconomicOperation.description: The present state of ECO mode operation, on(1) if system is on bypass due to ECO mode operation, off(0) any other time.

lgpPwrPreferredSource.name: lgpPwrPreferredSource
lgpPwrPreferredSource.description: The well known measurement source from the 'lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurements' sub-tree that is the preferred input source of the system.

lgpPwrLoadOnSource.name: lgpPwrLoadOnSource
lgpPwrLoadOnSource.description: The well known measurement source from the 'lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurements' sub-tree that is currently powering the output (load).

lgpPwrNominalVoltageDeviation.name: lgpPwrNominalVoltageDeviation
lgpPwrNominalVoltageDeviation.description: The nominal voltage deviation between the well known measurement source lgpPwrSource1Input and lgpPwrSource2Input.

lgpPwrNominalVoltageDeviationPercent.name: lgpPwrNominalVoltageDeviationPercent
lgpPwrNominalVoltageDeviationPercent.description: The percentage of the nominal voltage deviation between the well known measurement source lgpPwrSource1Input and lgpPwrSource2Input.

lgpPwrPhaseDifferenceLimit.name: lgpPwrPhaseDifferenceLimit
lgpPwrPhaseDifferenceLimit.description: The maximum phase difference (between the well known input sources ) in which a transfer to an available input source is permitted.

lgpPwrFrequencyDeviationLimit.name: lgpPwrFrequencyDeviationLimit
lgpPwrFrequencyDeviationLimit.description: The maximum frequency deviation (between the well known input sources ) in which a transfer to an available input source is permitted.

lgpPwrThresholdTable.name: lgpPwrThresholdTable
lgpPwrThresholdTable.description: A list of power thresholds for a given power measurement at a point/location in the system. The lgpPwrThresholdType in this table corresponds to the type of measurement the high and low thresholds applies to. This table contains zero, one, or many rows, depending upon the number of 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint' and 'lgpPwrThresholdSubID' available in the table. The NMS cannot create or delete rows from the table. The rows are created by the agent based upon the capabilities of the managed device.

lgpPwrThresholdEntry.name: lgpPwrThresholdEntry
lgpPwrThresholdEntry.reference: The lgpPwrThresholdType in this table corresponds to the type of measurement the high and low thresholds applies to.
lgpPwrThresholdEntry.description: This entry defines the contents of the columns for the table 'lgpPwrThresholdTable'.

lgpPwrThresholdIndex.name: lgpPwrThresholdIndex
lgpPwrThresholdIndex.description: This is the index indicating the row of the table 'lgpPwrLineMeasurementTable' for a power measurement point.

lgpPwrThresholdPoint.name: lgpPwrThresholdPoint
lgpPwrThresholdPoint.reference: The object identifiers in this column can be found in the sub-tree 'lgpPwrWellKnownMeasurementPoints' and correspond to the entry in the table 'lgpPwrThresholdTable'.
lgpPwrThresholdPoint.description: An OID representing a well known measurement point. These object identifiers indicate a point or location of power measurement in a power system. The OID's name usually implies a location of the measurement point such as 'input', 'output', 'bypass' etc.

lgpPwrThresholdSubID.name: lgpPwrThresholdSubID
lgpPwrThresholdSubID.description: This is a sub identifier for the 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint'. It indicates the instance number of the well known threshold point.

lgpPwrThresholdType.name: lgpPwrThresholdType
lgpPwrThresholdType.reference: The object identifiers in this column can be found in the sub-tree 'lgpPwrWellKnownThresholdTypes' and correspond to the entry in the table lgpPwrThresholdTable.
lgpPwrThresholdType.description: An OID representing a well known measurement type. These object identifiers indicate the type of measurement referenced by the row of the table. These object identifiers can encompass units of measure, lines of reference, and device location. The OID's name usually implies a measurement type such as 'voltsAc', 'current', 'voltsDc', 'VoltsLL', etc.

lgpPwrThresholdHighWarning.name: lgpPwrThresholdHighWarning
lgpPwrThresholdHighWarning.description: The high warning threshold of a type of measurement designated by the 'lgpPwrThresholdType' at a location designated by the 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint'. If multiple thresholds are available at a single 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint', of the same 'lgpPwrThresholdType', then the 'lgpPwrThresholdSubID' will differentiate between them. When this threshold is met, the agent will send a notification.

lgpPwrThresholdHighFailure.name: lgpPwrThresholdHighFailure
lgpPwrThresholdHighFailure.description: The high failure threshold of a type of measurement designated by the 'lgpPwrThresholdType' at a location designated by the 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint'. If multiple thresholds are available at a single 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint', of the same 'lgpPwrThresholdType', then the 'lgpPwrThresholdSubID' will differentiate between them. When this threshold is met, the agent will send a notification.

lgpPwrThresholdLowWarning.name: lgpPwrThresholdLowWarning
lgpPwrThresholdLowWarning.description: The low warning threshold of a type of measurement designated by the 'lgpPwrThresholdType' at a location designated by the 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint'. If multiple thresholds are available at a single 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint', of the same 'lgpPwrThresholdType', then the 'lgpPwrThresholdSubID' will differentiate between them. When this threshold is met, the agent will send a notification.

lgpPwrThresholdLowFailure.name: lgpPwrThresholdLowFailure
lgpPwrThresholdLowFailure.description: The low failure threshold of a type of measurement designated by the 'lgpPwrThresholdType' at a location designated by the 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint'. If multiple thresholds are available at a single 'lgpPwrThresholdPoint', of the same 'lgpPwrThresholdType', then the 'lgpPwrThresholdSubID' will differentiate between them. When this threshold is met, the agent will send a notification.

lgpPwrUpsAutoRestart.name: lgpPwrUpsAutoRestart
lgpPwrUpsAutoRestart.description: The device will automatically restart when utility power is restored following a battery discharge.

lgpPwrUpsAutoRestartDelay.name: lgpPwrUpsAutoRestartDelay
lgpPwrUpsAutoRestartDelay.description: The device will automatically delay a certain number of seconds and then restart after utility power is restored following a battery discharge. The number of seconds to delay is subject to the precision of the device and should be kept to 10 second intervals.

lgpPwrAutoRestartBatteryChargeThreshold.name: lgpPwrAutoRestartBatteryChargeThreshold
lgpPwrAutoRestartBatteryChargeThreshold.description: The battery charge percentage required before the device can automatically restart.

lgpPwrParallelModuleCount.name: lgpPwrParallelModuleCount
lgpPwrParallelModuleCount.description: The number of modules in the parallel system.

lgpPwrParallelRedundancyCount.name: lgpPwrParallelRedundancyCount
lgpPwrParallelRedundancyCount.description: The number of redundant modules in the parallel system.

lgpPwrLoadBusSyncMode.name: lgpPwrLoadBusSyncMode
lgpPwrLoadBusSyncMode.description: The configuration of Load Bus Synchronization (LBS) between independent systems.

lgpPwrEconomicOperationMode.name: lgpPwrEconomicOperationMode
lgpPwrEconomicOperationMode.description: The configuration of the economic operation mode of the system.

lgpPwrAutomaticBatteryTest.name: lgpPwrAutomaticBatteryTest
lgpPwrAutomaticBatteryTest.description: Automatic battery test option. If enabled, the battery will be tested on a fixed interval. If disabled, the battery test must be initiated by a battery test command. The interval at which a battery test is performed is defined by 'lgpPwrAutomaticBatteryTestInterval'.

lgpPwrMinimumRedundantPowerModule.name: lgpPwrMinimumRedundantPowerModule
lgpPwrMinimumRedundantPowerModule.description: The minimum number of redundant power modules that must be present before sending a loss of power redundancy alarm. If 0, there is no redundant power functionality.

lgpPwrMinimumRedundantBatteryModule.name: lgpPwrMinimumRedundantBatteryModule
lgpPwrMinimumRedundantBatteryModule.description: The minimum number of redundant battery modules that must be present before sending an alarm. If 0, the redundant battery module alarm is disabled.

lgpPwrOutputToLoadUserOverloadLimit.name: lgpPwrOutputToLoadUserOverloadLimit
lgpPwrOutputToLoadUserOverloadLimit.description: This is the user specified maximum load the device can support without sending an alarm.

lgpPwrNoLoadWarningLimit.name: lgpPwrNoLoadWarningLimit
lgpPwrNoLoadWarningLimit.description: The minimum current draw on the output in which the device considers there to be a load present on the output. The condition lgpConditionWarningNoLoadDetected will be triggered if the output current falls below this value. lgpPwrUpsTopOffline.name: lgpPwrUpsTopOffline
lgpPwrUpsTopOffline.description: The UPS has an offline topology. Under normal operating conditions, AC power from the utility passes straight through the UPS to the critical load. The inverter is used to convert the DC power from the battery to create AC power to support the load when the utility fails. Normally the inverter is operating in the stand-by mode, keeping the batteries charged. Should the utility power go out of specification, the inverter will power the load by drawing energy from the battery.

lgpPwrUpsTopLineInteractive.name: lgpPwrUpsTopLineInteractive
lgpPwrUpsTopLineInteractive.description: The UPS has a line-interactive topology. This topology resembles the offline product, but inserts a transformer or inductor in series between the utility power source and the load. This inline inductor enables the UPS inverter to interact with incoming power and provide a measure of power conditioning to the load. This buck-and-boost circuitry helps with high and low input voltage conditions.
